<number id="3D8E24E1CD07883681CDFF04FDE4FF46" box="[484,512,151,175]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D) plumose with thick solid tracts of oxeas, running mainly towards surface, branching off not very regularly. Tracts piercing the normal surface level and forming erect long conules. Tissue including large numbers of sigmas and sand grains.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936C6CD07883680EEFE97FE84FE6E" blockId="52.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80">
Spiculation (
<tableCitation id="C6C4037DCD0788368172FE97FE5EFEF5" box="[347,442,260,284]" captionStart="TABLE 14" captionStartId="52.[151,239,435,459]" captionText="TABLE 14. Spicule sizes of Microxina benedeni (Topsent, 1901). Values in µm are given as follows: minimum – mean – maximum (number of spicules measured). For comparison, values from Topsent (1901), Burton (1929) and Koltun (1964) are given." pageId="52" pageNumber="80">
Tab. 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD07883681B3FE97FE5EFEF5" box="[410,442,260,284]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="14.0">14</number>
</tableCitation>
): Main spicules almost straight oxeas (
<figureCitation id="137D2A43CD07883683B9FE97FC03FEF5" box="[912,999,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[155,1440,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 18. Microxina benedeni (Topsent, 1901), SMF 11836. A, habit in lateral view, B, habit in top-view. C, skeletal arrangement beneath the epidermal surface with echinating spicule bundles to the right, D, choanosomal skeleton. E, oxea. F – G. sigmas. Scale bars: A – B: 10 mm, C – D: 1 mm, E: 100 µm, F – G: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="80">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD07883683E2FE97FC03FEF5" box="[971,999,260,284]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
E) with sharp ends and a relatively characteristic shape, tapering straightly from thick centres to the ends. Oxeas 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD0788368425FEB4FB62FED6" box="[1036,1158,295,319]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="870.0" valueMax="980.0" valueMin="760.0">760 to 980</number>
µm long and 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD0788368501FEB4FA78FED6" box="[1320,1436,295,319]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="38.75" valueMax="42.5" valueMin="35.0">35 to 42.5</number>
µm in diameter. Microscleres exclusively c-shaped sigmas (
<figureCitation id="137D2A43CD078836836DFEDFFC72FE8D" box="[836,918,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[155,1440,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 18. Microxina benedeni (Topsent, 1901), SMF 11836. A, habit in lateral view, B, habit in top-view. C, skeletal arrangement beneath the epidermal surface with echinating spicule bundles to the right, D, choanosomal skeleton. E, oxea. F – G. sigmas. Scale bars: A – B: 10 mm, C – D: 1 mm, E: 100 µm, F – G: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="80">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD0788368353FEDFFC72FE8D" box="[890,918,332,356]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
F–G), 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD07883683C2FEDFFB90FE8D" box="[1003,1140,332,356]" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="55.0" valueMax="62.5" valueMin="47.5">47.5 to 62.5</number>
µm in length and 
<number id="3D8E24E1CD0788368565FEDFFF2CFE6E" pageId="52" pageNumber="80" value="25.0" valueMax="27.5" valueMin="22.5">22.5 to 27.5</number>
µm in width.
</paragraph>
